<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="428" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,973,1538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,973,998]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Despite its similarity with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[594,868,973,997]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Andrenosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albibarbe">
<emphasis box="[594,868,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Andrenosoma albibarbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Seguy" authorityYear="1952" box="[929,1180,973,997]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Andrenosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bayardi">
<emphasis box="[929,1180,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Andrenosoma bayardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the characteristics of male terminalia led us to confirm it as a valid species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="428" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,973,1538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1045,1070]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Description</emphasis>
. Medium size species (14 ̶ 
<quantity box="[654,740,1046,1070]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
), black and scarcely pilose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1063,1126,1045,1070]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Head</emphasis>
. Face, facial gibbosity and beard with white setae. Antennae with strong black setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[828,917,1081,1106]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Thorax</emphasis>
with black or white setae dorsally and long, strong, black, long setae laterally. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[532,614,1117,1142]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Wings.</emphasis>
First posterior cell open at wing margin (
<figureCitation box="[1078,1145,1117,1142]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1983,2006]" captionTargetBox="[368,1230,253,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[333,1262,214,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Wing (a) and Dististylus (b) of Andrenosoma: A. albibarbe (fig. 1); A. atrum (fig. 2); A. bayardi (fig. 3); A. biacuminatum (fig. 4); A. cyrtoxys (fig. 5)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/836078/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
a). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1180,1304,1117,1142]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites IV ̶VII are red medially. Black legs with white setae, most abundant on the coxae. Bright black male terminalia with gonostylus with a toothed blade on superior edge (
<figureCitation box="[740,809,1189,1214]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1983,2006]" captionTargetBox="[368,1230,253,1932]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[333,1262,214,1970]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Wing (a) and Dististylus (b) of Andrenosoma: A. albibarbe (fig. 1); A. atrum (fig. 2); A. bayardi (fig. 3); A. biacuminatum (fig. 4); A. cyrtoxys (fig. 5)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/836078/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
b). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[849,983,1189,1214]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">Variability.</emphasis>
Some specimens with black and white setae on facial gibbosity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,973,1538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="428">
Biology and ecology. Flight period from April to June. They perchin sunny forest clearings, mainly pine woods, between 
<quantity box="[338,402,1298,1322]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" unit="m" value="800.0">800m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[456,542,1297,1322]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="428" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
above sea level.
</paragraph>
